com.javatoavalla.stepfunction

Class StepFunctionArgsListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.javatoavalla.antlr.StepFunctionArgsBaseListener
      • com.javatoavalla.stepfunction.StepFunctionArgsListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StepFunctionArgsListener, org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.ParseTreeListener

    public class StepFunctionArgsListener
extends StepFunctionArgsBaseListener
    The StepFunctionArgsListener class extends StepFunctionArgsBaseListener and is responsible for processing and collecting argument terms used in step functions. It creates and stores JavaArgumentTerm objects that represent the arguments encountered during parsing.

    This listener populates a list of JavaArgumentTerm objects, each of which stores details about the argument's type, name, and whether it is primitive or not.

    Each JavaArgumentTerm is created when the enterArgument method is triggered, and added to the javaArgumentTermList when the exitArgument method is called.
